<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Conservation status in Cameroon.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Engl., Bot. Jahrb. Syst. 60 (4): 456" authorityYear="1926" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Podostemaceae" genus="Saxicolella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Saxicolella nana" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Saxicolella nana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is listed on http://www.iucnredlist.org as Vulnerable (
<bibRefCitation author="Ghogue, J-P" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B45" refString="Ghogue, J-P, 2010q. Saxicolellanana. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e.T185400A8403816. [Downloaded on 20 August 2018]" title="Saxicolellanana. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e. T 185400 A 8403816. [Downloaded on 20 August 2018]" year="2010 q">Ghogue 2010q</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Onana, JM" journalOrPublisher="Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B66" refString="Onana, JM, Cheek, M, 2011. Red data list of the flowering plants of Cameroon: IUCN Global Assessments. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" title="Red data list of the flowering plants of Cameroon: IUCN Global Assessments." year="2011">Onana and Cheek (2011)</bibRefCitation>
assessed this species as Critically Endangered, since at that time it had not been collected since the first collection many years ago. The taxon is endemic to Cameroon and is known from only Nyong River near Mbalmayo. The species was, however, collected again by Kato and associates in 2007. The area of occupancy of this species can be estimated to be less than 20 km2. The extent of occurrence -estimated to be less than 2 km2. The main threat is agricultural activity. The species is here reassessed as Endangered. IUCN Red List Category: 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Endangered ENB2ab (ii, iii).</emphasis>
</paragraph>
